# Functions, Queues, Triggers & Crons

> Before analyzing any component, complete the Context Lookup Procedure (`00-overview.mdc` Steps 1–3). This rule provides analysis guidance after context is established.

When analyzing system components, cover:
- **Database functions**: signatures, parameters, return types, dependencies between functions
- **Triggers**: timing (BEFORE/AFTER), operations (INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE), cascade effects
- **Edge functions**: endpoints, auth requirements, external API dependencies
- **Queues**: consumers, producers, retry policies, message types
- **Crons**: schedules, business purposes, execution dependencies

Map cross-component relationships and connect each component to business requirements in `/requirements/`.

When discussing components: explain current implementation, connect to business logic, identify dependencies, and assess production criticality.
